title: Young Israelis block aid to Gaza while IDF soldiers stand and watch
description: Secretary of State Antony Blinken has called on Israel to ensure the passage of aid into Gaza. But there’s no apparent effort to stop protesters from shutting a key crossing down.

title: Chile’s deadly wildfires wiped out neighborhoods. One stood unscathed.
description: A pilot project funded by the U.S. government showed it’s possible to fireproof a community, even amid historic destruction.

title: What to know about Lunar New Year: The Year of the Dragon
description: As a billion people in much of Asia and across the world celebrate Lunar New Year this weekend, here’s what to know about the auspicious Year of the Dragon.

title: Republicans are ‘owning’ the message of abandoning Ukraine
description: As a large bipartisan contingent of senators gets ready to attend a conference in Munich, lawmakers expect tough questions from European allies about U.S. support for Ukraine against Russia.

title: Could the Year of the Dragon bring the baby boom that Asia needs? Maybe.
description: In some parts of Asia, the Year of the Dragon, which starts Saturday, is considered an auspicious year to be born. Some hope that could mitigate low birth rates.

title: In Indonesia, an admired president faces sharp criticism over election
description: Joko Widodo, widely know as Jokowi, is not on the ballot in this week’s election but is seeking to preserve his legacy -- and his family’s influence.

title: Moody’s downgrades Israel’s credit rating, citing war in Gaza
description: The agency said Israel’s military campaign poses ongoing political and economic risks. Aid groups have condemned the country’s plan to remove civilians from Rafah.
